  <li id="comment-8231" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/05817049547134774699" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Pille</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/06/handy-to-have-around/#comment-8231"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-03-01T11:15:00-05:00">Saturday, March 1, 2008 at 11:15 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I must thank you again for an excellent recipe. I made these on Wednesday, using ordinary small onions (shallots are prohibitingly expensive here and hard to find anyway). 500 grams of onions (halved or quartered) for your amounts of oil and sherry vinegar, and you know what, they were absolutely delicious. K. was especially keen on them:) And they&#8217;re lovely cold, too &#8211; I had some on toasted and buttered rye bread this morning for breakfast:)</>So, THANK YOU! You&#8217;re a star!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    </ol>

      
  
